# Chapter 19 — The External Audit

*A local audit is a contained fire. An external audit from the Global Office is a nuclear strike. They don't look for bugs. They look for any reason to delete the entire project and start over from the backup.*

---

The news hit the 11th and 14th floors at exactly 10:00 AM. 

A fleet of black sedans had pulled up to the Pinnacle Systems building. Four people stepped out, all wearing identical charcoal suits, identical expressionless faces, and carrying identical silver briefcases. 

They weren't from the Manila office. They were from the Global Compliance Division in Singapore.

```
╔══════════════════════════════════════════╗
║               DANGER LEVEL: SS           ║
║                                          ║
║  Environment: THE GLOBAL AUDIT           ║
║  Objective: SURVIVE THE COMPLIANCE.      ║
║  Status: [ UNDER THE MICROSCOPE ]        ║
║                                          ║
║  Detection Meter: 60% [||||||    ]       ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

Juan dela Cruz stood by his window on the 14th floor, watching them enter. He could feel the weight of their presence through the floorboards. These weren't 'Workers' or even 'Executives'. They were 'Erasers'.

"They're here for the Phoenix Project," Cynthia said, walking into his office. She looked pale. "Victor Tan just called. Apex is happy with the implementation, but the Global Office is flagging the 'statistical anomalies' in our delivery speed."

"Isabel warned us," Juan said. "She said they don't like anomalies."

*Knock. Knock.*

This time, the knock wasn't a courtesy. It was a command. 

The door opened, and a man stepped in. He was tall, thin, and had eyes that looked like they were made of liquid crystal. Above his head, his Rank didn't just glow; it hummed.

```
╔══════════════════════════════════════════╗
║               BOSS ENCOUNTER             ║
║                                          ║
║  Name: MARCUS VANE (THE ERASER)          ║
║  Rank: SS (Global Compliance)            ║
║  Status: [ ABSOLUTE ]                    ║
║                                          ║
║  Special Attack: 'The Project Delete'    ║
║  (Can terminate any project instantly)   ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

"Mr. Dela Cruz," Marcus said, his voice perfectly neutral. "Ms. Ocampo. I am Marcus Vane. I am here to verify the integrity of the Phoenix Project."

He didn't sit. He didn't shake hands. He simply opened his silver briefcase and pulled out a small, glowing device that looked like a high-end scanner.

"The Global Office has noted that Project Phoenix has achieved in three weeks what should have taken six months. We have also noted the 'Aethelgard' whistleblower report. We are curious as to how a Rank-C Technical Manager and a Rank-A Architect managed to bypass S-Rank security protocols."

Marcus walked to Juan’s workstation. He waved the scanner over the keyboard.

```
║  ALERT: DETECTION METER: 60% → 75%       ║
║  [||||||||  ]                            ║
║  Marcus is scanning for 'Residual Shadow  ║
║  Energy'.                                ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

"Rodel," Juan whispered in his mind. "Hide. Deep. Cynthia, merge with the real one."

*"Too late, boss,"* Rodel’s voice was a jagged frequency. *"He’s using a 'Code-Purge' scanner. If I hide in the hardware, he’ll find me. I have to move to the network."*

"Go," Juan commanded.

As Rodel’s shadow blurred into the Ethernet port, Marcus’s scanner beeped. 

"Interesting," Marcus said, looking at the screen of his device. "There is a high concentration of non-linear data processing on this terminal. It’s almost as if the machine was being operated by someone who doesn't use a mouse or keyboard."

He looked at Juan, his liquid crystal eyes reflecting the blue windows of the System. 

"Are you a 'System Worker', Mr. Dela Cruz?"

The question was like a physical blow. Juan felt the Invisibility skill shatter. The Boardroom, the office, the 14th floor—it all seemed to fade away, leaving only the two of them in a void of cold, gray logic.

"I don't know what that is, sir," Juan said, his heart racing. "I’m a Technical Manager. I use the tools I’m given."

"Tools," Marcus repeated, a slight smile touching his lips. "The Global Office has its own tools. We call them 'The Founders'. And they’ve been looking for a 'Raise' in this region for a very long time."

```
║  ALERT: DETECTION METER: 85% [||||||||| ] ║
║  Marcus Vane is a 'System Seeker'.        ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

Marcus closed his briefcase. "You have twenty-four hours to prepare a full, manual demonstration of the Phoenix engine. No shadows. No 'optimizations'. Just you and your code. If the engine doesn't perform exactly as the implementation logs claim... the project will be deleted. And you will be 'Reset'."

He turned and walked out of the office, his presence leaving a wake of absolute silence.

Juan slumped into his chair. His STAMINA was at 5%. His shadows were scattered. And he had just been challenged to do the impossible: be human.

"Juan," Cynthia whispered, her hand on his shoulder. "What did he mean by 'Reset'?"

"It means the System doesn't just work for me," Juan said, looking at the flickering blue windows. "It works for them. And they’re about to audit my soul."

